DUAL LICENSE — paper text vs. analysis code
============================================

This repository is released under two licenses:

1. Paper text, figures, tables, and any other manuscript content
   (notably paper.tex, references.bib, figures/*.pdf,
   tables/*.tex) are licensed under the Creative Commons
   Attribution 4.0 International License (CC-BY-4.0).
   Full text: https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/4.0/legalcode

2. Analysis code (notably the contents of scripts/, requirements.txt,
   and any code embedded in REPRODUCING.md) is licensed under the
   MIT License, reproduced below.

Data files in data/ that consist of factual coordinates (river
centroids, paleocourse coordinates) are not copyrightable as such
and are placed in the public domain to the extent permitted by law,
WITH THE FOLLOWING EXCEPTIONS:

- The cached OSM responses in data/osm_cache/ are derived from
  OpenStreetMap data, which is © OpenStreetMap contributors and
  licensed under the Open Database License (ODbL); see
  https://www.openstreetmap.org/copyright for the terms of
  attribution and share-alike that apply to redistribution of
  OSM-derived data.

- The MERIT-Hydro-derived coordinates in
  data/river_coordinates_merit.csv (and any descendants) are
  derived from the MERIT-Hydro product (Yamazaki et al. 2019,
  Water Resources Research 55:5053-5073), which is distributed
  under Creative Commons Attribution-NonCommercial 4.0
  International (CC BY-NC 4.0). These derived coordinates
  inherit the non-commercial restriction. Cite Yamazaki 2019 in
  any downstream use. See
  https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc/4.0/ for the full
  CC BY-NC 4.0 terms.

